SCRIPT.MSCRI:
:P HOSTG# &HOSTG#
!make sure vara is a hostg type :SET &HND# = PREP_PROCESS_AGENTGROUP(&HOSTG#) :PROCESS &HND# : SET &AGENT# = GET_PROCESS_LINE(&HND#,1) : SET &STATUS# = GET_PROCESS_LINE(&HND#,2) : PRINT "Agent: &AGENT#" : PRINT "Status: &STATUS#" :ENDPROCESS :CLOSE_PROCESS &HND#
:PSET &RESULT# = &AGENT#

!Added 2012/05/22 - If the job is not activated via WorkFlow, ignore scripting on changing agent via promptset :SET &ACT_TYPE# = SYS_ACT_PARENT_TYPE(ACT) !ADDED Consultant Scott Hughes - 06/06/2018 !if &host# is not defined the variable will now contain null without overwriting so that below functions can fail gracefully - 06/06/2018 :SET &HOST# = &HOST# :SET &LEN# = STR_LENGTH(&HOST#) !Declaring AG so that we can see if it is a hostg - 06/06/2018 :SET &AG# = &HOST# :SET &HOST_TYPE# = GET_OBJECT_TYPE(&AG#)
:IF &HOST_TYPE# = "HOSTG" : SET &HND# = PREP_PROCESS_AGENTGROUP(&AG#,,BY_RULE)
: PROCESS &HND# : SET &OVERRRIDE_AGENT# = GET_PROCESS_LINE(&HND#,1) : PRINT "Resolved HOSTG(&AG#) to: &OVERRRIDE_AGENT#" :ENDPROCESS
:CLOSE_PROCESS &HND# :ENDIF
:IF &ACT_TYPE# = 'JOBP' : IF &LEN# > 0 : P "HOST is changing from &$AGENT# to &HOST# via HEADER.RA.USER.PRE" : PUT_ATT HOST = &OVERRRIDE_AGENT# : ENDIF :ENDIF
!DEPRECATED on 6/6/2018 - Scott Hughes !:IF &ACT_TYPE# = 'JOBP' ! !! This is for the testing for BECU "MONTHEND" (S#193756). Steps are below: !! 1) Operator chooses the Promptset to use at the ProcessFlow level !! 2) If the agent for the jobs within the PF is not an OSI agent, nothing is done. Otherwise: !! 3) A flag gets set to true that this is an OSI agent !! 4) If the flag is true !! 5) Print a message that the host is being changed from a header in Client 0 and run a PUT_ATT on the host !! !! Requirements: !! 1) This only works on OSI agents !! 2) There has to be a variable object called VARA.SQLI.LIST.ALL.OSI.AGENTS which lists all OSI agents !! 3) There has to be a promptset that chooses the agent. Here we use &HOST# as the promptset value ! !! Initiate the flag. It will always be false unless the agent is an OSI agent (look below) !: SET &AGENT_IS_OSI# = "FALSE" ! !! Loop through all OSI agent names !: SET &HND# = PREP_PROCESS_VAR(VARA.SQLI.LIST.ALL.OSI.AGENTS) !: PROCESS &HND# !! Get the OSI agent name from the variable !: SET &OSI_HOST# = GET_PROCESS_LINE(&HND#, 1) !! IF the current agent (&$AGENT#) is equal to the OSI agent name from the variable, we know it is an OSI agent and set the flag to true !: IF &$AGENT# = &OSI_HOST# !: SET &AGENT_IS_OSI# = "TRUE" !: ENDIF !: ENDPROCESS !: CLOSE_PROCESS &HND# !! If the job is an OSI job, run a PUT_ATT to change the host !: IF &AGENT_IS_OSI# = "TRUE" !: IF &HOST# <> '' !: P "HOST is changing from &$AGENT# to &HOST# via HEADER.RA.USER.PRE" !: PUT_ATT HOST = &HOST# !:ENDIF !: ENDIF !:ENDIF

SCRIPT.MSCRI: :SET &NULL# = David :SET &NULL# = &NULL# :SET &LEN# = STR_LENGTH(&NULL#) :P &LEN#
! :INCLUDE JOBI.UNIX.LOAD, NOFOUND=IGNORE

:SET &v_event_message# = GET_ATT(EVENT_FILE_PATH) :SET &v_event_host# = GET_ATT(HOST) ! :IF STR_FIND(&v_event_message#,'*') > 0 : SET &fhnd# = PREP_PROCESS_FILENAME('&v_event_host#','&v_event_message#','Y') : PROCESS &fhnd# : SET &v_event_message# = GET_PROCESS_LINE(&fhnd#,1) : P &v_event_host# / &v_event_message# : PUT_READ_BUFFER v_event_host# = '&v_event_host#' : PUT_READ_BUFFER v_event_message# = '&v_event_message#' : SET &runnr# = ACTIVATE_UC_OBJECT('JOBS.KROUSETLP.ACCUZIP_PUSH_CUST_FILE') : ENDPROCESS :ELSE : SET &cmd# = 'stat &v_event_message#' : SET &hnd# = PREP_PROCESS(&v_event_host#,UNIXCMD,"Modify:","CMD=&cmd#","COL=DELIMITER","DELIMITER=':'","UC_LOGIN=LOGIN.LINUX") : PROCESS &hnd# : SET &date# = GET_PROCESS_LINE(&hnd#,2) : SET &date# = STR_TRIM(&pid#) : IF &date# <> &file_mod_date# : IF &file_mod_date# ="" : P "Filedate for &v_event_message# was empty, changed to &date#." : ELSE : P "Filedate for &v_event_message# has changed from &file_mod_date# to &date#." : P &v_event_host# / &v_event_message# : PUT_READ_BUFFER v_event_host# = '&v_event_host#' : PUT_READ_BUFFER v_event_message# = '&v_event_message#' : SET &runnr# = ACTIVATE_UC_OBJECT('JOBS.KROUSETLP.ACCUZIP_PUSH_CUST_FILE') : PSET &file_mod_date#=&date# : ENDIF : ENDIF : ENDPROCESS :ENDIF

SCRIPT.MSCRI: :P &COUNT# :P &NAME# :P &STATUS#

! insert these lines in your script to determine if an error occurred ! ! @set retcode=%errorlevel% ! @if NOT %ERRORLEVEL% == 0 goto :retcode
!get client specific api key :SET &KEY# = GET_VAR(VARA.API_KEYS,"5005") :P &KEY#
:BEGIN_EXT_INTERPRETERS POWERSHELL
<# .SYNOPSIS Can be used to send events to the Automic Event Engine .DESCRIPTION Use this cmdlet to send events to the Automic Event Engine. It's making use of the Invoke-RestMethod commandlet and preconfigures everything. Creates the timestamp for the event automatically (current utc timestamp). .PARAMETER Uri The Uri to the endpoint for the events .PARAMETER Token The pre-shared key used for authentication with the Uri .PARAMETER Type The type of the Event, must match the Event Definition in the AE .PARAMETER Attributes The attributes of the event .PARAMETER Timestamp The timestampe (Event time) of the event, if empty current time in utc is used, timestamp will be converted to utc. .PARAMETER DisableKeepAlive Indicates that the cmdlet sets the KeepAlive value in the HTTP header to False. By default, KeepAlive is True. KeepAlive establishes a persistent connection to the server to facilitate subsequent requests. .PARAMETER Proxy Specifies that the cmdlet uses a proxy server for the request, rather than connecting directly to the Internet resource. Enter the URI of a network proxy server. .PARAMETER ProxyCredential Specifies a user account that has permission to use the proxy server that is specified by the Proxy parameter. The default is the current user. Type a user name, such as "User01" or "Domain01\User01", or enter a PSCredential object, such as one generated by the Get-Credential cmdlet. This parameter is valid only when the Proxy parameter is also used in the command. You cannot use the ProxyCredential and ProxyUseDefaultCredentials parameters in the same command. .PARAMETER ProxyUseDefaultCredentials Indicates that the cmdlet uses the credentials of the current user to access the proxy server that is specified by the Proxy parameter. This parameter is valid only when the Proxy parameter is also used in the command. You cannot use the ProxyCredential and ProxyUseDefaultCredentials parameters in the same command. .EXAMPLE $data = @{ Name="Tobi" Status="New" Count=3 } C:\PS>send-event "http://path_to_ia/" "your-pre-shared-key" "IA.TEST" $data This will send the $data to the Event "IA.TEST" ($data is converted to json)
.NOTES Author: Tobias Stanzel Date: June 17, 2017 #> function Send-Event { [CmdletBinding()] param ( [parameter(Mandatory=$true,Position=0)] [Uri]$Uri,
[parameter(Mandatory=$true,Position=1)] [string]$Token,
[parameter(Mandatory=$true,Position=2)] [alias("t")] [string]$Type,
[parameter(Mandatory=$true,Position=3)] [alias("a")] [hashtable]$Attributes,
[parameter(Mandatory=$false)] [DateTime]$Timestamp,
#Invoke-RestMethod Options [parameter(Mandatory=$false)] [Int32]$TimeoutSec,
[parameter(Mandatory=$false)] [switch]$DisableKeepAlive,
[parameter(Mandatory=$false)] [Uri]$Proxy,
[parameter(Mandatory=$false)] [PSCredential]$ProxyCredential,
[parameter(Mandatory=$false)] [switch]$ProxyUseDefaultCredentials ) PROCESS { if(!$Timestamp){ $Timestamp = Get-Date; } $utcString = $Timestamp.ToUniversalTime().ToString("yyyy-MM-ddTHH:mm:ss.fffZ"); Write-Verbose "Event time set to: $utcString"
$Body = @{ type = $type timestamp = $utcString values = $attributes } $BodyString = ConvertTo-Json($Body)
$headers = @{ "Content-Type"="application/json";Authorization=$Token} $params = @{ Method = "Post" Headers = $headers Uri = $Uri Body = $BodyString } if($VerbosePreference) { $params.Verbose = $true } if($DebugPreference) { $params.Debug = $true } if($DisableKeepAlive) { $params.DisableKeepAlive = $true } if($TimeoutSec) { $params.TimeoutSec = $TimeoutSec } if($Proxy) { $params.Proxy = $Proxy if($ProxyCredential) { $params.ProxyCredential = $ProxyCredential } if($ProxyUseDefaultCredentials) { $params.ProxyUseDefaultCredentials = $true } } Write-Verbose "Headers: $(ConvertTo-Json($headers))" Write-Verbose "Body: $BodyString" try { Invoke-RestMethod @params Write-Host "Event $type send successfull" } catch { # Dig into the exception to get the Response details. # Note that value__ is not a typo. Write-Host "StatusCode:" $_.Exception.Response.StatusCode.value__ Write-Host "StatusDescription:" $_.Exception.Response.StatusDescription Throw $_.Exception } } } echo "Sending hardcoded event now via powershell cmdlet to Event Engine now..." $data = @{ Name="Test Event" Status="New" Count=4 } send-event "http://vwaanalytics01:8090/analytics/api/v1/events" "&KEY#" "PS.TEST.EVENT" $data -v echo "Sending event again, with different count" $data.count = 4 send-event "http://vwaanalytics01:8090/analytics/api/v1/events" "&KEY#" "PS.TEST.EVENT" $data -v
:END_EXT_INT POWERSHELL
:P &COUNT# :P &NAME# :P &STATUS#
